<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-84-0652 </DOCNO><TEXT>The author discusses the options available for implementing the NuclearWaste Policy Act (NWPA) of 1982. The author concludes that the federaland state governments must cooperate because this is a political problem.Two sites must be selected because this gets the Western states supportingthe act and provides a backup if problems develop at one site. The authorsays once 2-4 sites are chosen as finalists, an educational campaignmust be done in those states to stress safety. Solving the waste problemwill give the nuclear industry a brighter future.</TEXT></DOC>